<h2 id="why-choose-this-course">Why choose this course?</h2>
<p>Embarking on a journey into climate science is more vital than ever. Our planet faces unprecedented challenges and Australia is a climate hotspot with diverse landscapes—from the Great Barrier Reef to the arid outback. By studying climate science here, you’ll engage with real-world scenarios: heatwaves with record-high temperatures, longer fire seasons and extreme fire danger days, reduced average rainfall and prolonged droughts, increased heavy rainfall events, and coastal storm surge inundation and erosion. These climate hazards will impact Australia''s social cohesion, human health and wellbeing, environment, infrastructure and economy (<a href="https://www.dcceew.gov.au/sites/default/files/documents/national-climate-risk-assessment-first-pass-assessment-report_2.pdf" target="_blank">National Climate Risk Assessment</a>),</p>
