<div class="panel-content">
<h2 id="why-choose-this-course">Why choose this course?</h2>
<p>Jobs in the medical engineering field are on the rise due to a strong fous on research and development in medical technologies, the expanding healthcare industry, and ongoing advancements in medical tech and devices (Engineers Australia Labour Market Overview). </p>
<p>With a medical engineering degree from QUT, you’ll join a dynamic and growing industry that’s changing the future of healthcare. From ensuring the safe operation of medical equipment, to designing and developing innovative medical devices, you’ll apply your engineering expertise to improve global health outcomes. </p>
<p>QUT staff, students and alumni are leaders in the dynamic field of medical engineering. Some of our graduates who have gone on to achieve amazing things include Daniel Timms, founder of the world’s first artificial heart, and Chris Jeffries, founder and CEO of medical device company Field Orthopaedics. </p>
